<HEADLINE>
Former Chinese FM Li Zhaoxing receives honorary doctoral degree
from Hong Kong Baptist  University
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
HONG KONG, Nov. 15 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Chinese Foreign Minister Li Zhaoxing was given an honorary doctoral
degree in Humanities on Monday by the Hong Kong Baptist University for his
achievements as a diplomat and contributions to China.
</P>
<P>
Besides Li, physicist Sir John Pendry was awarded with the degree of Doctor of
Science, honoris causa. Artist Van Lau was awarded the degree of Doctor of
Letters, honoris causa. Ir Wong Kwok- keung was recognized with the degree of
Doctor of Social Sciences, honoris causa. Professor Zhang Boli was granted the
degree of Doctor of Science, honoris causa.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hong Kong Baptist University, Li, who became the Chinese
ambassador to the United States of America in 1998, had helped China and the
U.S. set up permanent normal trade relations.
</P>
<P>
And as Chinese foreign minister between 2003 and 2007, Li had actively advocated
"public diplomacy" and taken measures to support the concept. Nowadays, these
measures have become traditions of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Albert Chan, who became president of the Hong Kong Baptist University this July
and was officially inaugurated in the day, commended the five honorary doctors,
saying that their achievements and contributions to society would serve as an
excellent model and a source of great encouragement and inspiration for everyone
at the University.
</P>
</TEXT>
