<DOC id="XIN_ENG_20101124.0024" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
Syrian president meets Armenian parliament chairman on bilateral
ties
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
DAMASCUS, Nov. 24 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Syrian President Bashar al-Assad met with Hovik Abrahamyan, the Armenian
parliament's chairman, here on Monday, discussing the historical bilateral
relations binding the two countries, the Syrian official SANA news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The talks also tackled parliamentary cooperation between Damascus and Yerevan
and people-to-people ties.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also touched upon the latest developments in the Middle East and
the Caucasus region, particularly the halted peace process between Arabs and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Prime Minister Mohammed Naji Otri also discussed with Abrahamyan
cooperation and friendly relations between Syria and Armenia in the economic,
cultural and social fields.
</P>
<P>
The speakers of parliament of Armenia and Syria signed a memorandum of
understanding on further development and reinforcement of friendly ties and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Armenian President Serzh Sargsyan visited Syria in March and held talks with
Syrian officials on regional and international developments.
</P>
<P>
Abrahamyan and his delegation arrived in Syria Monday evening on a three-day
official visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
